description: The new CHAMELEON takes center stage as MAJOR BLUDD starts making serious moves, upping his game and wreaking havoc on the Joes! And all the while, Steeler is caught smack in the middle of all the pandemonium that is COBRA CIVIL WAR!
name: Cobra Civil War Part 15

description: THE YOUNG MASTERS MEET THE YOUNGEST MASTER! This summer’s surreal sojourn into good and evil bursts into Loki’s world – and the little trickster is ready to teach the next generation of evil he’s no longer on their side! But worse for them, MS. AMERICA is with him! The Teen Brigade and The Young Masters collide as Joe Casey and Nick Dragotta continue the year’s longest, strangest trip!
name: Drive All Night

description: It started with their new acquaintance, Sally, found brutally slain in her kitchen. And most recently: two rival gangs, lifeless bodies sprawled across a basketball court, a noose around each of their necks. Hot on the trail of a serial killer who’s lynching his victims, the mutant detectives of X-Factor Investigations are eager to cut his killing spree short. But here’s hoping they find him before he finds them!

Sonja's clever campaign against Emora enters a new phase, as her best laid plans come to fruition. Just as the sons of the empire are at each others throats, Emperor Antonious asserts his power. Meanwhile Sonja learns that to overthrow an empire you need a little help from your friends.

Spider-Woman has been exposed as a double-agent - but why has she betrayed the New Avengers to Hydra? Find out here!

By Brian Michael Bendis and Frank Cho.

Also: the Super-Android strikes!

By Joe Casey and Will Rosado.

Plus: the Vision goes wild in a classic tale by David Michelinie and George Pérez.

100 page special!

The leaders of top superteams have been working together in secret for years - but now the Illuminati are revealed!

By Brian Michael Bendis and Jim Cheung.

Plus: the New Avengers go public, and face their most dangerous enemy yet - an angry J. Jonah Jameson!

By Brian Michael Bendis and Frank Cho.

Also: the Young Avengers return at last! But will Captain America shut them down for good?

By Allan Heinberg and Andrea DiVito.

Colonel Steve Austin’s body is ruined, his spirit broken, the prospect of a future as a barely human cyborg haunting him as he hovers between life and death. Meanwhile, the demented cyborg Hull launches the first strike in his fanatical war against humanity! From the team that brought you Kevin Smith’s Green Hornet.
name: Chapter 3: We Can Rebuild Him

description:
The power of the Collective finds a new target - and Magneto is reborn! The New Avengers face disaster in Genosha in the staggering climax of this adventure!

By Brian Michael Bendis and Mike Deodato Jr.

Plus: the Kree and Skrull empires both want Hulkling! The Young Avengers are caught in an interstellar crossfire!

By Allan Heinberg and Jim Cheung

Also: Captain America battles Zemo in the finalé of Avengers Under Siege!

By Roger Stern and John Buscema.

100-page anniversary special!

The New and Young Avengers unite at last to confront the combined might of the Kree and Skrull Empires! Don't miss an epic battle!

By Allan Heinberg and Jim Cheung.

Plus: the origin of the mysterious Illuminati is finally revealed - as the assembled heroes prepare for the superhero Civil War!

By Brian Michael Bendis and Alex Maleev.

Now that Hugo Strange is in control of Arkham City, he's even more eager to make sure every criminal is locked away...yet Catwoman and Two-Face are still on the lam. Strange gets a hot tip on Catwoman's location, setting off a chain of double-crosses, robberies and brawls! How will Batman factor into this fight, especially since Strange is looking for him, too?
name: Inside Job (Part 1)

description: The DARKWING DUCK/DUCKTALES crossover event twenty years in the making picks up from DUCKTALES #5 here — with this issue marking Part 2 of “Dangerous Currency.” Whatever happened to Fenton Crackshell, the original Gizmoduck? Darkwing Duck and visiting Duckburg tycoon Scrooge McDuck intend to find out…that is, if they don’t disappear themselves! Second to last issue—with DARKWING DUCK #18 coming out the same month. It’s the end of an era as KABOOM! says goodbye this month to Disney in a final epic story spanning DARKWING DUCK #17, DUCK TALES #6 and DARKWING DUCK #18.
name: Dangerous Currency: Part 2

description: The time has come.

The Statue of Liberty has been in the United States since the late 1800's and has seen millions of people come and go over the years. But, you bet she's never seen this: an army of gargoyles perched atop her arms, her robes, and her crown, ready to leave Manhattan and spread an ancient pandemic across the entire United States! Only one man can stop this outbreak, and SWAT officer Jon Griffin had better hurry -- because the United States Government is less than an hour away from dropping a bomb on New York City!
name: Scorched

description: The pairing you never thought could happen! IDW Publishing and DC Comics are proud to present the greatest tale of the 23rd century! Or is that the 31st century? As you'll see here, it's both. Eisner-nominated writer Chris Roberson and Star Trek and Legionnaires veteran artist Jeffrey Moy partner up to bring you the most bizarre partnership of any century! In this first issue, a group of Legionnaires end up lost in the 23rd century, but it's a universe that isn't familiar to either the Legion or the crew of the USS Enterprise!
name: Part One

description: Everything you've ever wanted to know about the cast of The Walking Dead. The Survivor's Guide is a handy checklist of all the characters who have appeared in the series thus far, alive or dead. This series is a can't-miss supplement to the hit comic book series that is now a hit TV series on AMC! Collecting the 4-issue mini series, The Walking Dead Survivors' Guide.
name: TPB

description:
Are you addicted to aliens? Late night Encounters? Abductions? Probes? The XenoHolics are here to help!

Because everyone thinks they're a bunch of nutcases, a support group that claims aliens abducted them try to prove that aliens are real. But that's much easier said than done and they find themselves caught up in not just ONE government conspiracy, but TWO. Oh, yeah and along the way they learn who is lying about being abducted? and who is telling the truth.

Presenting a twisted new series about aliens and the crazy people who believe in them, by creators JOSHUA WILLIAMSON (Superman/Batman, DEAR DRACULA), and SETH DAMOOSE (I HATE GALLANT GIRL) with covers by DAN DUNCAN (TMNT)
name: Xenoholics

description: In the vault of the Russian Occult Bureau's headquarters is a man chained down and heavily monitored. When Kate and Johann are brought in for assistance, the zombie director of the Russian bureau pits them against the possessed prisoner!
name: 2 (of 5)

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: From the pages of WILDC.A.T.S comes this seductive (suggested for mature readers) collection of the popular miniseries written by Alan Moore (WILDC.A.T.S.: HOMECOMING, BATMAN: THE KILLING JOKE). Featuring stunning art by Michael Lopez, Al Rio, Edwin Rossell, and Trevor Scott, this story follows the most sensual of all the WildC.A.T.s on her return to her home town of New Orleans, where she quickly lands a job as an exotic dancer at the Midnight Lounge. But dancers have been disappearing from the Lounge, victims of a killer seeking supernatural powers through the dancers' deaths. Is Voodoo destined to be the next victim? Or is she the one person who can close the door forever on this nightmare? Includes a gallery collecting the stunning miniseries cover art by Michael Lopez and Adam Hughes.
name: Voodoo: Dancing in the Dark

description: A young woman wakes up in a hospital in Nepal with amnesia. As she struggles to find answers on her identity, she finds criminals on her tail and that she has an uncanny skill set that suggest she may be an international spy.

Starlord Summer Special from 1978, with new comic strips, features (sci-fi movies of the 1950's), interviews (Gerry Anderson on Thunderbirds) and vehicle cut-aways (Ro-Busters Preying Mantis).

Cover artist: unknown

  • TimeQuake (Patterson - John Cooper)
  • Ro-Busters (Kelvin Gosnell - Geoff Campion)
  • Trash (D Hooper - Magano)
  • Strontium Dog (Chris Lowder - Brendan McCarthy)
name: Starlord Summer Special 1978

description:
First of three Starlord Annuals. As with all British annuals, the date on the cover is the following year. This annual was released in the summer of 1979. There are no writer/artist credits in the annual.

Cover artist: unknown

  • Inside front cover - Starlord (art: Ian Gibson)
  • Strontium Dog - Funfair of Fear (art: Brendan McCarthy)
  • Ro-Busters
  • Captain Condor and the Forbidden Planet (reprint from Lion)
  • Jimmi from Jupiter (reprint from Lion)
  • The Metal Men (reprint)
  • Day of the Droids (text story)
  • The Midas Touch (text story)
  • TimeQuake
  • Val Venture - Peril at the Cente of the Earth! (reprint from Tiger)
  • Tharg's Future Shocks - Prisoner of Xendor
  • Invaders from Jupiter (reprint)
name: Starlord Annual 1980

description: Nick Fury has sent Hawkeye on a vital international mission. But with no backup to be had, Clint Barton may find himself on the losing end of a major battle—until Fury sends in unexpected reinforcements: a covert mutant team and The Hulk!
name: Part Three of Four

description:
A new saga begins: WAR OF THE HULKS!!! Skaar, son of the Hulk, comes to Earth! The stage is set for an epic battle between the two gamma-powered monsters, with the Fantastic Four and She-Hulk caught in the middle! Don’t miss the beginning of a year-long story that will rock the Marvel Universe!

Also: Ronin and the Young Avengers take on Loki, and the Mighty Avengers battle the Unspoken!

Plus: The Punisher clashes with a mind-controlled, homicidal Spider-Man!

Includes material reprinted from Mighty Avengers #29, Planet Skaar: Prologue #1, Skaar Son of Hulk #11-12 and Punisher Annual #1.

‘War of the Hulks’ continues! The mysterious Red Hulk is here, and he wants the green Hulk to die! Guest-starring Spider-Man and She-Hulk!

Also: The Mighty, Secret and Young Avengers join forces against the Unspoken – and the Wasp discovers his true purpose in life from the awesome Eternity!

Includes material reprinted from Incredible Hulk #600-601 and Mighty Avengers #30.
